body:
Values in queues seem to persist, even though queue is declared at the beginning of the loop. I tested only in class-based code, inside a function.

```systemverilog
// Minimal testcase to demonstrate Verilator bug with dynamic arrays
// persisting values between for loop iterations

class test_class;

    function void demonstrate_bug();

        // This should create fresh queues for each iteration
        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) begin
            int values[$]; // Our queue declaration under test

            $display("Iteration %0d:", i);
            $display("  values.size() at start: %0d", values.size());

            // Add some values
            values.push_back(i);
            values.push_back(i + 10);

            $display("  After adding: values=%p, names=%p", values);
            $display("  values.size() at end: %0d", values.size());
            $display("");
        end
    endfunction

endclass

module tb_verilator_queue_bug;

    task automatic check_issue();
        test_class tc = new();
        tc.demonstrate_bug();
    endtask

    initial begin
        check_issue();
        $finish;
    end

endmodule
```

verilator command used to run the example: 
```shell
verilator --binary -Wall -Wno-fatal --top-module tb_verilator_queue_bug verilator_bug_test.sv
./obj_dir/Vtb_verilator_queue_bug
```

Expected result (Xcelium 23 output):
```output
Iteration 0:
  values.size() at start: 0
  After adding: values='{0, 10}
  values.size() at end: 2

Iteration 1:
  values.size() at start: 0
  After adding: values='{1, 11}
  values.size() at end: 2

Iteration 2:
  values.size() at start: 0
  After adding: values='{2, 12}
  values.size() at end: 2
```

Actual result (Verilator):
```output
Iteration 0:
  values.size() at start: 0
  After adding: values='{'h0, 'ha}
  values.size() at end: 2

Iteration 1:
  values.size() at start: 2
  After adding: values='{'h0, 'ha, 'h1, 'hb}
  values.size() at end: 4

Iteration 2:
  values.size() at start: 4
  After adding: values='{'h0, 'ha, 'h1, 'hb, 'h2, 'hc}
  values.size() at end: 6
```

Correctly, values are not persisted across function calls to `check_issue` or `tc.demonstrate_bug()`. But they are persisted on for-loop iterations.
I used Verilator version Verilator 5.039 devel rev v5.038-249-gca2c40347, on Fedora42 running on WSL2.

